quote.text:
I don't agree. I think people are overestimating Bitcoin. The tech is not that great, but the high price clouds people's thinking, especially when it goes up as that triggers people's greed.

But the fact is that it's very flawed:

- No financial privacy due to its transparent ledger
- Lacks fungibility for the same reason
- Slow confirmation times
- High transaction fees
- No ability to handle many transactions due to its small block size 
- Poor long-term security because of the falling block reward, which will lead to the miners going elsewhere
- Very centralized these days because of ASICs/mining farms

Bitcoin was a great proof of concept, but these days it's very overhyped. 

I prefer Monero (XMR). There is a reason why it's starting to overtake BTC in terms of usage.
